    nursingActions: ["Assess AV access for thrill and bruit before and after each treatment", "Obtain pre-treatment vital signs and weight", "Monitor vital signs every 15-30 minutes during treatment", "Manage intradialytic hypotension: lower ultrafiltration rate, give NS bolus, Trendelenburg", "Hold antihypertensive medications before dialysis to prevent hypotension", "Assess for signs of air embolism (dyspnea, chest pain, cyanosis)", "Apply pressure to access sites after treatment for hemostasis", "Obtain post-treatment weight and vital signs"],
